THE Walt Disney Company, which owns theme parks, resorts and a Hollywood
studio, yesterday reported a 25 per cent rise in net profits to Dollars
204.9m for the second quarter of its fiscal year, ended on March 31, writes
Alan Friedman. Earnings per share were 23 per cent higher at 38 cents, while
operating income climbed by 50 per cent to Dollars 406.6m. Revenues were 24
