<HEADLINE>
FT  27 APR 93 / Photos 'cut card fraud by 99%'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AN EXPERIMENT in etching photographs and signatures on cheque guarantee
cards cut fraud by nearly 99 per cent, the Royal Bank of Scotland said
yesterday, John Gapper writes.
The bank, which has 1m customers, said it intended to be the first British
bank to offer them all the chance to have photographs on cards.
The laser etching of photographs and signatures on the reverse of the bank's
Highline cheque guarantee, cash dispenser and debit cards, costs about
Pounds 1.20 per card, about three times the cost of conventional cards.
