Mr Alex Barr, Royal Bank's card services development manager, said it was
also considering trying to put photographs on its credit cards. It would
have to negotiate this with First Data Resources, which makes its credit
cards.
He conceded that the bank's competitive advantage would probably be eroded
if other banks adopted similar tactics. At present most other financial
services companies are working together on new card fraud prevention
measures.
Mr Barr said 31,500 of the 100,000 customers offered cards in the pilot had
applied for them. The bank expected a similar proportion of all its
customers to take up the offer, but they would be free to choose.
