<HEADLINE>
FT  27 APR 93 / Resignation throws Brazilian presidential election wide open
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINA LAMB
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   RIO DE JANEIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE leader of Brazil's largest political party announced his resignation
from the job last night. This surprise from Mr Orestes Quercia throws open
the field for the country's presidential election next year, writes
Christina Lamb in Rio de Janeiro.
He has long been under pressure to quit as head of the Democratic Movement
party (PMDB), in response to allegations of much corruption during his
recent governorship of Sao Paulo state. However, he was thought to have
stayed on course for his party's presidential candidacy.
</TEXT>
