FT  27 APR 93 / US company opens in Hanoi
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HANOI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
An American consulting firm opened for business in Hanoi yesterday, the
first US company to operate officially in Vietnam since the end of the war
in 1975, AP reports from Hanoi.
Vietnam America Trade and Investment Consulting Co will advise other
companies interested in penetrating Vietnam's market of 70m people. It says
clients include Chrysler.
At least two other US companies - Bank of America and a consultancy called
Ashta International - have also obtained licences to open representative
offices in Vietnam.
